# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# .zEnv - Environment Configuration for WebSocket Demos
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# This file stores sensitive configuration values that should NEVER be hardcoded.
# zCLI automatically loads this file and makes variables available via zConfig.
#
# Security Best Practices:
#   1. Store tokens/secrets in .zEnv (not in Python code)
#   2. Add .zEnv to .gitignore (never commit secrets)
#   3. Use different tokens for dev/staging/production
#   4. Rotate tokens regularly
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

